<h1 class="hero-h">AI for salons and spas: <em>the practical 2026 playbook.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Salons run on a full book and a steady social presence. AI makes the retention messaging and daily content cheap to keep up, even with a small team behind the desk. The practical playbook follows.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short version</div><p class="verdict-p">Salons get the most from AI on rebooking and retention messages, social content, review responses, and front-desk replies. Start with Claude Pro ($20/mo) plus the messaging in Vagaro, GlossGenius, or Fresha. Budget under $100/mo. The retention and content time savings pay it back quickly.</p></div>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Where AI actually moves the needle for salons</h2>
<p class="body">An empty chair is lost revenue you cannot recover. The fix is consistent rebooking and visibility, and that is exactly what AI makes easy.</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Rebooking and retention messages.</strong> Draft personalized rebooking reminders, win-back texts, and birthday or loyalty offers that fill the gaps in next week's book.</li>
<li><strong>Social content.</strong> Turn before-and-after photos and new services into a week of captions and reels scripts, so the feed that attracts new clients stays active.</li>
<li><strong>Review responses.</strong> Draft on-brand replies to Google reviews in seconds, keeping your rating and local search strong.</li>
<li><strong>Front-desk replies.</strong> Draft fast, friendly answers to DMs and inquiries about services, pricing, and availability so leads do not go cold.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">The lesson from <a href="/ai-for-small-business">AI for small business</a> fits: automate the messaging and content, keep the chair-side experience human.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Recommended starting stack</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Claude Pro ($20/mo)</strong> for retention messages, captions, and replies.</li>
<li><strong>Vagaro, GlossGenius, or Fresha</strong> for booking, automated reminders, and client lists.</li>
<li><strong>Instagram scheduling</strong> to batch a week of content at once.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">Under $100 a month for most salons. For wider cost context, see <a href="/how-much-does-claude-cost">what Claude costs</a>.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">The ROI math</h2>
<p class="body">Twenty minutes a day on social and client messages is over two hours a week. AI batches it down to about 20 minutes total, and the retention lift matters more: a few extra rebookings a week is real money against a sub-$100 tool bill. More in <a href="/how-much-does-ai-marketing-cost">how much AI marketing costs</a> and <a href="/save-time-with-ai-small-business">how small businesses save time with AI</a>.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">What AI should not do for a salon</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Send client texts without a quick read. Tone and timing matter for rebooking.</li>
<li>Make claims about results or products it cannot stand behind.</li>
<li>Auto-reply to complaints. Sensitive messages need a human.</li>
<li>Replace your stylists' voice and relationships, which are why clients come back.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the best AI tool for a salon?</div><div class="faq-a">Claude Pro ($20/mo) for retention messages and social, paired with Vagaro, GlossGenius, or Fresha. Under $100/mo for most salons.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How can a salon use AI to fill its book?</div><div class="faq-a">Consistent rebooking reminders and win-back messages. AI drafts the personalized texts and offers that pull clients back into next week's openings.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Can AI run salon social media?</div><div class="faq-a">It can draft a week of captions and reel scripts from your photos and services in minutes. A human still picks the images and adds personality.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is AI worth it for a small salon?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. The content and retention work is the same at any size, so a small team gets back the most relative time.</div></div>
</div></section>

